{{Infobox language |name=Diodio |altname=West Goodenough |states=[[Papua New Guinea]] |region=[[Milne Bay Province]] (Goodenough Island) |speakers={{sigfig|2180|2}} |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Western Oceanic languages|Western Oceanic]] |fam5=[[Papuan Tip languages|Papuan Tip]] |fam6=[[Nuclear Papuan Tip languages|Nuclear Papuan Tip]] |fam7=[[North Papuan Mainland – D'Entrecasteaux languages|North Papuan Mainland – D'Entrecasteaux]] |fam8=Bwaidoga |iso3=ddi |glotto=diod1237 |glottorefname=Diodio }}
'''Diodio''', or '''West Goodenough''', is an [[Austronesian]] language spoken in [[Milne Bay Province]], [[Papua New Guinea]], on [[Goodenough Island]], which it shares with [[Bwaidoka language|Bwaidoka]], Iduna, and Kaninuwa.
