{{Infobox language |name=Hukumina |nativename=Bambaa |region=[[Buru Island]], Moluccas |state=Indonesia |extinct=(1 speaker in 1989) |ref=<ref>Grimes, "Buru (Masarete)", in Tsuchida, ed., 1995, ''Comparative Austronesian Dictionary''</ref> |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Nuclear Malayo-Polynesian languages|Nuclear MP]] |fam4=(unclassified; possibly [[Buton languages|Buton]]) |dia1=Palumata |dia2=Bara |iso3=huw |glotto=huku1237 |glottorefname=Hukumina }}
'''Hukumina''' is an extinct and unclassified [[Austronesian language]] recently spoken in the northwest of [[Buru Island]] in the [[Maluku Islands]] of eastern [[Indonesia]]. However, it may not have been one of the indigenous [[Buru languages]] but an old migration from [[Buton Island]] off the southeast coast of [[Sulawesi]], and thus possibly a [[Buton languages|Buton language]].
