{{Infobox FBI Ten Most Wanted | name = Terry A. D. Strickland | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1992|2|15}} | birth_place = Illinois | charge = Homicide, unlawful flight to avoid prosecution | alias = Teery A. Strickland, Terry A. Strickland, Terry Antonio Strickland | occupation = Laborer | nationality = American | gender = Male | added_date = December 15, 2016 | caught_date = January 15, 2017 | remove_date = | number = 512 | status = Caught }}
'''Terry A. D. Strickland''' (born February 15, 1992) is an American who is charged for the murder of two men in July 2016. On December 15, 2016, Strickland was added to the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]]'s [[FBI Ten Most Wanted Fugitives|Top Ten Most Wanted]] list. Strickland was arrested in El Paso, Texas on January 15, 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nbcchicago.com/news/local/fbi-strickland-milwaukee-homicide-top-10-most-wanted-407968315.html|title=Illinois Man on Top 10 Most Wanted List for Double Homicide|last=Ray|first=Richard|date=December 22, 2016|work=|newspaper=NBC Chicago|access-date=January 14, 2017|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/fbis-10-most-wanted-terry-d-strickland-has-been-called-cold-blooded-killer-here-why-he-tops-710427|title=FBI's 10 Most Wanted: Terry A D Strickland has been called a 'cold blooded' killer; here is why he tops the list|last=Bhat|first=Aditya|date=|work=|newspaper=[[International Business Times]], India Edition|language=en|access-date=2017-01-14|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.jsonline.com/story/news/crime/2016/12/15/fbi-adds-suspect-milwaukee-double-homicide-most-wanted-list/95482294/|title=FBI adds suspect in Milwaukee double homicide to most wanted list|last=Luthern|first=Ashley|date=December 15, 2016|work=|newspaper=[[Milwaukee Journal Sentinel]]|access-date=January 14, 2017|via=}}</ref>
== Capture == Strickland was arrested in [[El Paso, Texas]] on January 15, 2017 by city FBI agents and policemen. He was apprehended without incident during a traffic stop at 5:10 a.m. [[Mountain Standard Time|MT]] and booked into the El Paso county jail. The FBI's public tip line was contacted earlier in the month suggesting that Strickland was living in the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elpasotimes.com/story/news/crime/2017/01/15/fbi-most-wanted-fugitive-arrested-el-paso/96613996/|title=FBI Most Wanted fugitive arrested in El Paso|publisher=}}</ref><ref>Kelly McCleary and Tony Marco. [http://www.cnn.com/2017/01/15/us/terry-strickland-fbi-most-wanted-arrest/index.html One of FBI's Most Wanted suspects captured in Texas]. CNN. January 16, 2017.</ref>
